canonical:
  title: 端午日如晦設壽席于春暉亭令兒女隊爲鞦韆戲亦有比丘尼來參者
  author: 成俔
  language: lzh
  text: 靑娥皓齒笑空姸浪作人間謝自然強屈春心寄蘭若還隨女伴闘鞦韆霜袍日照鵝毛嫰烏帽風輕燕翼翩忽訝微塵成凈界如來方便散花天
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 端午日如晦設壽席于春暉亭令兒女隊爲鞦韆戲亦有比丘尼來參者
  author: 成俔
  language: lzh
  text: 靑娥皓齒笑空姸。浪作人間謝自然。強屈春心寄蘭若。還隨女伴闘鞦韆。霜袍日照鵝毛嫰。烏帽風輕燕翼翩。忽訝微塵成凈界。如來方便散花天。
korean:
  title: 단오일에 여회가 춘휘정에서 수연을 베풀고, 아녀를 시켜 짝을 지어 그네 놀이를 하는데, 비구니가 참여하는 자도 있었다
  author: 성현
  language: kor
  text: |-
    푸른 눈썹과 흰 이의 웃음이 고운데
    헛되이 사람이 되어 자연을 하직했네
    봄의 마음을 억지로 굽혀 난야(절간)에 붙였다가
    다시 여자의 짝을 따라 추천을 다투노라
    상포에 해가 비추매 거위털처럼 부드럽고
    오모에 바람이 가벼우매 제비 날개같이 펄럭인다
    갑자기 의심하나니 이 티끌 세계를 정계로 만들려고
    여래가 방편으로 하늘꽃을 흩날리는가
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1430_010_1160&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: 'On the Fifth Day of the Fifth Month: A Birthday Feast at Spring Radiance Pavilion, Where Men and Women Form Pairs to Swing, and Some Buddhist Nuns Also Participated'
  author: Sung Hyeon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Green eyebrows and white teeth—such radiant smiles,
    Yet they renounced the world, forsaking nature's design.
    They bent their springtime hearts toward the temple's refuge,
    Then danced again with their companions on the swings.

    White robes catch the sun's glow, soft as downy geese,
    Black caps flutter lightly in the wind, like swallows' wings.
    Suddenly I wonder: does the Buddha, through compassionate means,
    Scatter celestial flowers to transform this dusty realm into paradise?
  footnotes:
    - Nuns participate in this secular celebration, creating tension between their monastic vows and momentary worldly joy—the poem's central paradox.
    - The image of swinging represents both the lightness of returning to childhood and the cyclical nature of life between worldly and spiritual concerns.
    - The Buddha's 'skillful means' (方便, upaya) refers to the Buddhist teaching method of adapting truth to suit different audiences—here suggesting that even worldly pleasures may serve spiritual awakening.
